The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 15 November is 102,033 (11,759.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 10 November, there were 4,043 new confirmed cases (466.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 03 November, there were 4,532 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 11% (489 fewer cases).
